Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga to release the TALIS (Teaching and Learning International) South Africa report. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. PRETORIA - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga will announce the results of the Teaching and Learning International Survey (Talis) on Tuesday. The Talis covers about 260,000 teachers in 15,000 schools across 48 countries and economies. READ: Basic Education Department slams call to arm teachers The study investigates the conditions and learning environment in schools in countries including Australia, Japan, South Korea, Norway, the US and the UK. The report is viewed as an examination of the Basic Education sector from the perspective of the teachers.